Please Select Senior Citizen Concession Option.

Ministry of Railways has introduced give up scheme with regards to concession granted to Senior Citizen of Indian Nationality. As per the scheme, Senior Citizen passenger who wants to give up concessional ticket fare amount may do so now.\10Senior Citizen can opt “Forgo Concession” option, to give up the element of concessional amount upto 50%.
Thank you for forgoing Senior Citizen Concession.

What is LOWER BERTH/Sr. CITIZEN Quota??\10 LOWER BERTH/Sr. CITIZEN Quota berths are lower berths earmarked only for male of age 60 years and above/female of age 45 years and above, when traveling alone or two passengers (under mentioned criteria) traveling on one ticket.\10For reservation of pregnant women traveling alone under LOWER BERTH/Sr. CITIZEN Quota, booking facility is available only at Indian Railways Booking counters/Reservation Offices.

Specially abled and Journalist passengers availing the concession need to carry Photo Identity card issued by Railways which is to be produced for On-board / off-board verification during journey. Escort passengers also need to carry photo identity card mentioned at the time of booking.
